==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weeping tree
<hw>Weep"ing tree</hw>. <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Any tree having pendulous
branches.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A tree from which honeydew or other
liquid secretions of insects drip in considerable quantities, esp. one
infested by the larvae of any species of the genus <gen>Ptylus</gen>,
allied to the cuckoo spits, which in tropical countries secrete large
quantities of a watery fluid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>weeping tree broom</ent>⟦br⟧
